This paper investigates the correlation between demographics and the text of queries submitted to search engines, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also touches upon social implications and fairness in search engine use, which could be categorized under social and information sciences (cs.SI). The analysis of language use in search queries could also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the study involves the use of data and statistical analysis, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SD).
